## Steps

### step 1
id: navigate-to-patients
instruction: Click "Patients" in the main sidebar under the "Directory" section.
success_criteria: You are on the Patients page with a searchable table. Each row shows patient name, date of birth, biological sex, and status (Active/Inactive).
anchor: "Patients"
on_success: next
on_stuck: "Patients" is in the sidebar under "Directory." The Directory section may be collapsed — click it to expand.

### step 2
id: search-for-patient
instruction: Click the search bar and type the patient's first or last name. The table filters in real-time as you type.
success_criteria: The table shows only patients matching your search.
anchor: "search bar"
on_success: next
on_stuck: The search bar is above the patient table.

### step 3
id: open-patient-record
instruction: Click on the correct patient row to open their full record. If multiple results appear, use the date of birth column to confirm the right patient.
success_criteria: You are on the patient detail page showing demographics, summary tiles (encounter count, denials, documents), and tabs for Overview, Encounters, Documents, Authorizations, and History.
anchor: "patient row"
on_success: completion
on_stuck: Click anywhere on the patient row.

## Completion Message
patient record is open. you can see all their encounters, documents, and prior authorizations from here.

